race.comment: Things haven't gone to plan for SURPRISE COMING (6) in a couple of runs this campaign but he looks ready to peak third-up to the mile. He maps to get the perfect run to stick it out over 1600m. He can win and looks a nice play at each-way odds. Victorian visitor PORTER (1) was good in a strong BM70 race last start and profiles like he will appreciate the rise to 1600m. Expect him to be fighting out the finish. SNOOPY NOW (2) is a Stakes winner and if he turns up anywhere near his best, he's going to be hard to beat. The rise to 1600m looks perfect for him. KOMACHI (3) keeps racing well and must be considered, while HARD PRINCE (7) drops back in grade and rises slightly in trip, both of which are in his favour.
